      type: "Selective serotonin reuptake inhibitor (SSRI)",
      action: "S-enantiomer of racemic citalopram; the most selective SSRI for SERT binding with minimal off-target receptor activity; allosteric binding site on SERT enhances and prolongs serotonin reuptake inhibition beyond what primary site binding alone provides",
      sideEffects: "Nausea, insomnia, sexual dysfunction, dose-dependent QTc prolongation (maximum recommended dose 20 mg/day; 10 mg/day in patients >65 years, hepatic impairment, or CYP2C19 poor metabolizers), headache, weight gain with long-term use",
