        rationale: "Sertraline has the most safety data in pregnancy (preferred SSRI in pregnancy), lowest CYP2D6 inhibition (important since sumatriptan is partially metabolized by CYP2D6), and broad FDA-approved indications for anxiety disorders. Paroxetine is category D (contraindicated in pregnancy)."
